%S A116141 4,5303944,6677714,2070936216988528558,2969428172738875624,
%T A116141 6685545813563350444,8013829604553736451395958429212,
%U A116141 9724110515510343256451213152382
%N A116141 Numbers k such that k concatenated with k-2 gives the product of two numbers which differ by 1.
%C A116141 If k has d digits, the concatenation is k//k-2 = 10^d*k+k-2 = m*(m+1), therefore k//k-4 = 10^d*k+k-4 = (m-1)*(m+2), so there is a large overlap with A116128, and k//k-8 = 10^d*k+k-8 = (m-2)*(m+3), so there is a large overlap with A116105. - _R. J. Mathar_, May 22 2026
%e A116141 6677714//6677712 = 8171728 * 8171729, where // denotes
%e A116141 concatenation.
%Y A116141 Cf. A116134, A054214, A116154, A116272.
%K A116141 nonn,base,changed
%O A116141 1,1
